20Bengal%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20number%20of%20permanent%20workers%20engaged%20in%20the%20jute%20mills%20of%20Bengal%20%E2%80%93%20once%20a%20flourishing%20industry%20%E2%80%93%20have%20been%20on%20the%20decline%20for%20the%20past%2010%20years.%20The%20scores%20of%20workers%20whom%20%3Cem%3EThe%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EWire%3C%2Fem%3E%20spoke%20to%20in%20the%20district%20and%20outside%20say%20that%20out%20of%20permanent%2C%20special%20and%20temporary%20classes%20of%20workers%2C%20mill%20owners%20are%20keen%20on%20employing%20the%20most%20number%20of%20new%20people%20in%20the%20last%20category%20alone.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuch%20workers%20are%20known%20as%20%E2%80%9Czero%20number%E2%80%9D%20workers%20%E2%80%93%20their%20employment%20identity%20number%20is%20effectively%20zero%20because%20they%20are%20not%20registered%20with%20the%20mill.%20Such%20workers%20are%20often%20sent%20to%20mills%20by%20agencies%2C%20which%20are%20controlled%20by%20layers%20of%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWith%2075%20out%20of%20104%20jute%20mills%20located%20in%20the%20state%2C%20Bengal%20is%20still%20the%20hub%20of%20the%20Indian%20jute%20industry%20valued%20at%20Rs%2010%2C000%20crore.%20According%20to%20the%20Jute%20Commission%20of%20India%20records%2C%20as%20of%20December%2031%2C%202022%2C%20there%20are%20approximately%2046%2C487%20permanent%20workers%20and%201%2C08%2C461%20contractual%20workers%20working%20in%20the%20jute%20industry%20in%20India.%20However%2C%20beyond%20the%20record%20books%2C%20over%203%20lakh%20people%20are%20associated%20with%20the%20jute%20mills%20%E2%80%93%20unofficially.%20Two%20in%20three%20workers%20are%20working%20contractually%20in%20jobs%20that%20give%20little%20other%20than%20a%20basic%20income%20when%20there%20is%20work.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBharat%20Ram%20says%20his%20grandfather%20left%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20and%20came%20to%20the%20jute%20town%20of%20Bhatpara%20to%20work%20at%20a%20mill%20during%20the%20British%20rule.%20A%20third-generation%20jute%20mill%20worker%2C%20Bharat%20still%20works%20in%20the%20factory%20where%20his%20grandfather%20did.%20But%20he%20is%20one%20of%20the%20lucky%20few%20with%20a%20permanent%20job%20at%20the%20mill.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CAlmost%20all%20jute%20mill%20workers%20stay%20in%20slums%20%E2%80%93%20which%20should%20give%20you%20an%20idea%20of%20how%20they%20are%20paid.%20Contractual%20workers%20get%20as%20low%20Rs%20200%20per%20day%20in%20some%20mills%2C%20much%20lower%20than%20the%20minimum%20wage%20for%20unskilled%20workers%20in%20Bengal.%20But%20officially%2C%20there%20is%20no%20record%20of%20most%20of%20them%2C%E2%80%9D%20Bharat%20says.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20was%20%E2%80%9Cit%20was%20different%20earlier%E2%80%9D%20and%20every%20worker%20was%20eligible%20for%20provident%20fund%20contributions%2C%20gratuity%2C%20and%20employees%E2%80%99%20state%20insurance%20benefits.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EShame%2C%20cleanliness%20%E2%80%98distant%E2%80%99%20concepts%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHarendra%20Prasad%20Yadav%2C%20another%20generational%20jute%20mill%20worker%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%20points%20to%20the%20rot%20in%20the%20system%20and%20claims%20that%20while%20news%20is%20made%20when%3Cspan%3E%20jute%20mills%20are%20closed%20due%20to%20workers%E2%80%99%20agitations%2C%20government%20incentives%20all%20go%20to%20the%20mill%20owners.%20%E2%80%9COur%20condition%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20improve%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%20Retired%20for%20years%20now%2C%20Harendra%20is%20yet%20to%20receive%20his%20gratuity%20benefits.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20269px)%2085vw%2C%20269px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F26112540%2FScreenshot-2024-02-26-at-11.15.18%25E2%2580%25AFAM-885x1024.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22269%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F26112540%2FScreenshot-2024-02-26-at-11.15.18%25E2%2580%25AFAM-885x1024.png%20885w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F26112540%2FScreenshot-2024-02-26-at-11.15.18%25E2%2580%25AFAM-259x300.png%20259w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F26112540%2FScreenshot-2024-02-26-at-11.15.18%25E2%2580%25AFAM.png%201037w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-698861%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22311%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20gutter%20run%20through%20a%20workers%E2%80%99%20colony%20in%20Bhatpara%2C%20Bengal.%20Photo%3A%20Joydeep%20Sarkar.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHarendra%20shares%20his%20quarters%20with%20his%20son%2C%20two%20grandsons%2C%20and%20a%20daughter-in-law.%20On%20both%20sides%20of%20the%20narrow%20lanes%20that%20lead%20to%20his%20house%2C%20there%20are%20rows%20of%20similar%20cramped%20rooms.%20A%20foul-smelling%20sewer%20gutter%20cleaves%20the%20alley%20in%20two.%20This%20is%20a%20playground%20for%20children%20by%20day%2C%20and%20a%20shared%20toilet%20by%20night.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20are%20around%2060%2C000%20jute%20mill%20workers%20in%20the%20North%2024%20Parganas%20district%20alone.%20Nestled%20within%20the%20shadows%20of%20towering%20jute%20mills%20are%20the%20workers%E2%80%99%20colonies%20in%20which%20almost%20all%20of%20them%20live.%20Within%20each%20workers%E2%80%99%20colony%20is%20at%20most%20a%20single%20common%20bathroom%20without%20any%20doors%20or%20curtains.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20Janki%20Ram%2C%20a%20mill%20worker%2C%20the%20Swachh%20Bharat%20Abhiyan%20%E2%80%93%20the%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20flagship%20cleanliness%20drive%20%E2%80%93%20seems%20a%20distant%20dream.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CAlthough%20we%20have%20a%20ditch%20right%20at%20our%20doorstep%2C%20even%20the%20%5Bmosquito-borne%5D%20dengue%20is%20afraid%20to%20come%20here%2C%E2%80%9D%20jokes%20Janki.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKamli%20Devi%E2%80%99s%20son%20works%20at%20the%20factory.%20She%20says%20that%20for%20women%20in%20the%20colonies%20who%20struggle%20with%20the%20concept%20of%20a%20single%20shared%20toilet%2C%20shame%20is%20distant%20concept%20too.%20%E2%80%9C%3Cspan%3EWe%20can%E2%80%99t%20even%20afford%20to%20raise%20your%20voice%20against%20the%20mill%20owner%2C%20otherwise%20we%20will%20be%20driven%20away%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20309px)%2085vw%2C%20309px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F26112429%2FScreenshot-2024-02-26-at-11.15.33%25E2%2580%25AFAM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22309%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F26112429%2FScreenshot-2024-02-26-at-11.15.33%25E2%2580%25AFAM.png%20822w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F26112429%2FScreenshot-2024-02-26-at-11.15.33%25E2%2580%25AFAM-260x300.png%20260w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-698858%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22356%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20jute%20workers%E2%80%99%20colony.%20Photo%3A%20Joydeep%20Sarkar.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWorkers%20out%20of%20work%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20local%20member%20of%20parliament%2C%20Arjun%20Singh%2C%20says%20that%20he%20has%20spoken%20to%20%3Cspan%3Emany%20jute%20mill%20owners%20about%20the%20problem%2C%20%E2%80%9Cbut%20no%20one%20has%20done%20anything.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWhatever%20allegations%20the%20workers%20are%20making%20are%20right.%20The%20condition%20of%20jute%20mill%20colonies%20is%20primitive.%20Jute%20mills%20never%20run%20at%20a%20loss.%20The%20owners%20usurp%20the%20rights%20of%20the%20workers%20from%20their%20provident%20fund%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Singh.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESingh%2C%20known%20for%20his%20strong-arm%20tactics%20in%20the%20area%2C%20was%20a%20longtime%20Trinamool%20Congress%20leader%20but%20quit%20the%20party%20in%202019%20to%20win%20the%20Barrackpore%20Lok%20Sabha%20constituency%20as%20a%20BJP%20candidate.%20In%202022%2C%20he%20returned%20to%20his%20former%20party%20over%20the%20jute%20price-cap%20issue%20which%20led%20to%20the%20closure%20of%20about%20a%20dozen%20mills%20sending%20more%20than%2060%2C000%20workers%20out%20of%20work.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWith%20the%20majority%20of%20voters%20in%20the%20Barrackpore%20Lok%20Sabha%20constituency%20belonging%20to%20the%20working%20class%2C%20jute%20is%20an%20evocative%20issue%20that%20no%20political%20party%20can%20overlook.%20In%20its%20prime%2C%20the%20jute%20belt%20encompassing%20North%2024%20Parganas%2C%20Hooghly%2C%20and%20Howrah%20attracted%20thousands%20of%20workers%20from%20Bihar%2C%20Odisha%2C%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20and%20Madhya%20Pradesh.%20However%2C%20a%20considerable%20number%20have%20since%20returned%2C%20with%20hundreds%20of%20local%20labourers%20either%20choosing%20low-skill%20jobs%20or%20migrating%20to%20other%20states%20in%20pursuit%20of%20employment%20opportunities.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EJiten%20Majhi%2C%20who%20used%20to%20be%20a%20worker%20at%20a%20closed%20mill%2C%20is%20all%20set%20to%20move%20to%20south%20India%20for%20better%20opportunities.%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3EBhai%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20situation%20in%20Bengal%20has%20changed%20completely.%20We%20used%20to%20consider%20this%20place%20as%20one%20we%20could%20live%20out%20our%20futures%20in%20simply%20for%20the%20work%20opportunities%20it%20provided%2C%20but%20now%20there%20is%20not%20much%20hope%2C%E2%80%9D%20Jiten%20says.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20413px)%2085vw%2C%20413px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F26112408%2FScreenshot-2024-02-26-at-11.15.44%25E2%2580%25AFAM-1024x985.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22413%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F26112408%2FScreenshot-2024-02-26-at-11.15.44%25E2%2580%25AFAM-1024x985.png%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F26112408%2FScreenshot-2024-02-26-at-11.15.44%25E2%2580%25AFAM-300x289.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F26112408%2FScreenshot-2024-02-26-at-11.15.44%25E2%2580%25AFAM.png%201110w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-698857%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22397%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EJute%20bags.%20Photo%3A%20Joydeep%20Sarkar.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPrice%20and%20fall%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20January%20this%20year%2C%20the%20Bengal%20and%20union%20government%2C%20in%20a%20tripartite%20agreement%20with%20jute%20industry%20representatives%20and%20labour%20unions%2C%20revised%20the%20minimum%20daily%20wage%20for%20entry-level%20labourers%20from%20Rs%20370%20to%20Rs%20485.%20The%20revision%20came%20after%20five%20years%20but%20did%20not%20fulfil%20the%20demands%20of%20a%20minimum%20monthly%20wage%20of%20Rs%2026%2C000%2C%20the%20inclusion%20of%20all%20workers%20in%20the%20master%20roll%2C%20and%20the%20introduction%20of%20a%20system%20which%20would%20only%20have%20permanent%20and%20special%20%3Cem%3Ebadlee%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Eor%20transferrable%2C%20workers.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20jute%20industry%20is%20controlled%20by%20the%20Union%20government.%20The%20government%20does%20not%20have%20the%20willingness%20to%20do%20anything.%20However%2C%20we%E2%80%99re%20not%20able%20to%20give%20it%20the%20required%20importance.%20In%20my%20opinion%2C%20there%20should%20be%20a%20workers%E2%80%99%20movement%20against%20the%20gross%20neglect%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20former%20Communist%20Party%20of%20India%20(Marxist)%20MP%20and%20trade%20union%20leader%20Taritbaran%20Topdar.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EJute%20is%20primarily%20procured%20by%20the%20Union%20government%20for%20food%20grain%20packaging.%20A%20government%20regulation%20mandates%20100%25%20jute%20bag%20usage%20for%20food%20grains%20and%2020%25%20for%20sugar.%20However%2C%20current%20government%20orders%20for%20jute%20bags%20(1.48%20lakh%20bales%20in%20October-November)%20fell%20short%20of%20the%20previous%20volumes%20(3.50%20lakh%20bales).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F26112347%2FScreenshot-2024-02-26-at-11.15.39%25E2%2580%25AFAM-1024x703.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F26112347%2FScreenshot-2024-02-26-at-11.15.39%25E2%2580%25AFAM-1024x703.png%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F26112347%2FScreenshot-2024-02-26-at-11.15.39%25E2%2580%25AFAM-300x206.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F26112347%2FScreenshot-2024-02-26-at-11.15.39%25E2%2580%25AFAM.png%201104w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-698856%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22577%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EJute%20workers%20at%20a%20factory.%20Photo%3A%20Joydeep%20Sarkar.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CDue%20to%20the%20high%20demand%20for%20wheat%2C%20farmers%20are%20selling%20through%20the%20open%20market%2C%20thus%20reducing%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20need%20for%20jute%20bags%20for%20food%20grain%20storage.%20That%20is%20why%20despite%20a%20bumper%20crop%2C%20farmers%20are%20struggling%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Raghavendra%20Gupta%2C%20chairman%20of%20the%20Indian%20Jute%20Mills%20Association.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESynthetic%20bags%20have%20also%20flooded%20the%20market%2C%20alleges%20%3Cspan%3ERitabrata%20Banerjee%2C%20state%20president%20of%20the%20All%20India%20Trinamool%20Trade%20Union%20Congress.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20effort%20has%20been%20on%20for%20decades.%20Now%20they%20are%20trying%20to%20bring%20in%20a%20new%20variety%20called%20poly-jute%20which%20is%20also%20said%20to%20be%20environmentally%20friendly.%20A%20section%20of%20businessmen%20from%20western%20India%20is%20exerting%20influence%20on%20the%20Union%20government%20in%20this%20regard.%20The%20jute%20industry%20is%20not%20only%20suffering%20from%20the%20lack%20of%20action%20by%20the%20Union%20government%20but%20also%20from%20wrong%20policies%2C%E2%80%9D%20Banerjee%20says.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20government%20has%20set%20a%20minimum%20support%20price%20of%20Rs%205%2C400%20per%20quintal%20for%20jute%20in%20the%20current%20year.%20However%2C%20reports%20indicate%20that%20farmers%20are%20often%20receiving%20less%2C%20averaging%20around%20Rs%204%2C200%20or%20Rs%204%2C500%20per%20quintal%2C%20with%20prices%20falling%20even%20lower%20in%20some%20areas.%20While%20the%20number%20licensed%20warehouses%20authorised%20to%20buy%20and%20store%20jute%20stand%20at%206%2C000%2C%20the%20number%20of%20unlicensed%20entities%20engaging%20in%20direct%20jute%20purchases%20from%20warehouses%20has%20reportedly%20risen%20above%2032%2C000%20in%20the%20current%20year.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20frustration%20of%20the%20farmers%20is%20palpable.%20Sanuallah%2C%20a%20jute%20cultivator%20from%20Cooch%20Behar%2C%20expressed%20the%20challenge%20of%20finding%20fair%20prices%20after%20years%20of%20dependence%20on%20the%20crop.%20%E2%80%9CFor%20years%2C%20we%20have%20poured%20our%20sweat%20and%20toil%20into%20this%20crop.%20With%20current%20prices%2C%20the%20future%20of%20this%20cultivation%20remains%20uncertain%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESamar%20Biswas%2C%20a%20jute%20farmer%20from%20Karimpur%20in%20Nadia%20district%20echoes%20the%20same%20sentiment.%20%E2%80%9CDelhi%E2%80%99s%20orders%20have%20been%20slashed%2C%20so%20mill%20owners%20are%20now%20forcing%20us%20to%20sell%20our%20produce%20at%20Rs%202%2C500%20or%20face%20dire%20consequences.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Biswas%20voted%20for%20BJP%20in%20the%202019%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20the%202021%20assembly%20elections%2C%20but%20the%20issue%20of%20fair%20prices%20resonates%20across%20political%20allegiances.%20%E2%80%9CWhile%20we%20may%20remain%20loyal%20to%20Modi%20%3Cem%3Eji%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20loyalty%20cannot%20sustain%20empty%20stomachs%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708927715000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F26112616%2FUntitled-design-1-5.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Fjute-mills-bengal-labour-india-out-of-work%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22With%2075%20out%20of%20104%20of%20India's%20jute%20mills%20located%20in%20the%20state%2C%20Bengal%20is%20still%20the%20hub%20of%20the%20Indian%20jute%20industry%2C%20valued%20at%20Rs%2010%2C000%20crore.%20However%2C%20its%20workers%20are%20perpetually%20at%20a%20disadvantage.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A7%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Fjute-mills-bengal-labour-india-out-of-work%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Gong%20Myung%2C%20Weki%20Meki%E2%80%99s%20dating%20rumors%20debunked%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708927271000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-108001389%2Cimgsize-31210.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indi