022%20and%20July%202023%2C%20provides%20insights%20into%20household%20consumption%2C%20highlighting%20poverty%20levels%20and%20the%20effectiveness%20of%20poverty%20alleviation%20measures%20implemented%20by%20the%20government.%20Mr%20Subrahmanyam%20said%20that%20the%20survey's%20data%20on%20household%20consumption%20is%20a%20key%20metric%20for%20evaluating%20the%20success%20of%20poverty%20reduction%20initiatives.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20HCES%20findings%20reveal%20an%20increase%20in%20consumption%2C%20with%20both%20rural%20and%20urban%20areas%20experiencing%20a%20surge%20of%20about%202.5%20times.%20The%20average%20monthly%20per%20capita%20consumption%20expenditure%20(MPCE)%20in%20urban%20households%20rose%20by%2033.5%20per%20cent%20since%202011-12%20to%20Rs%203%2C510%2C%20while%20rural%20India%20witnessed%20a%20significant%2040.42%20per%20cent%20increase%2C%20reaching%20Rs%202%2C008.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBased%20on%20this%20data%2C%20poverty%20levels%20in%20the%20country%20could%20be%20closer%20to%205%25%20or%20less%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Subrahmanyam%20said%2C%20as%20per%20a%20%3Cem%3ETOI%20%3C%2Fem%3Ereport.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20key%20observations%20from%20the%20survey%20is%20the%20shift%20in%20spending%20patterns%2C%20particularly%20in%20terms%20of%20food%20expenditure.%20Rural%20households%2C%20for%20the%20first%20time%2C%20allocated%20less%20than%2050%20per%20cent%20of%20their%20total%20expenditure%20to%20food%2C%20according%20to%20the%20survey.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20survey%20claims%20that%20the%20urban-rural%20consumption%20divide%20has%20narrowed%20from%2091%25%20in%202004-05%20to%2071%25%20in%202022-23%2C%20signifying%20a%20reduction%20in%20inequality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20food%2C%20consumption%20of%20beverages%2C%20processed%20food%2C%20milk%20and%20fruits%20is%20growing%20-%20an%20indication%20of%20more%20diverse%20and%20balanced%20consumption%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Subrahmanyam%20said%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Sub