topped%20by%20the%20immigration%20authorities%20and%2C%20after%20a%2024-hour%20ordeal%20in%20a%20%E2%80%9Cholding%20cell%E2%80%9D%2C%20deported%20to%20London%20without%20being%20given%20any%20reason%20behind%20the%20action.%20Kaul%20holds%20a%20British-Overseas%20Citizenship%20of%20India%20passport.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20with%20%3Cem%3EThe%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EWire%3C%2Fem%3E%20from%20London%2C%20Kaul%20said%20that%20she%20was%20%E2%80%9Ctaunted%E2%80%9D%20for%20her%20critique%20of%20the%20Rashtriya%20Swayamsevak%20Sangh%20(RSS)%20%E2%80%93%20the%20ideological%20fountainhead%20of%20the%20ruling%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20%E2%80%93%20and%20its%20leaders%20by%20immigration%20officials%20who%20did%20not%20give%20any%20reason%20in%20writing%20for%20her%20deportation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20did%20say%20to%20the%20immigration%20officials%20that%20India%20is%20not%20China%20%E2%80%93%20it%20is%20supposed%20to%20be%20a%20democracy%20and%20therefore%20this%20kind%20of%20behaviour%20is%20completely%20unacceptable%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20told%3Cem%3E%20The%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20officials%20claimed%20that%20they%20had%20%E2%80%9Corders%20from%20Delhi%E2%80%9D%20to%20stop%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20deportation%20of%20Kaul%2C%20a%20Kashmiri%20Pandit%20who%20has%20criticised%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20watering%20down%20of%20Article%20370%2C%20is%20likely%20to%20shine%20light%20on%20the%20crackdown%20on%20free%20speech%20and%20the%20shackling%20of%20the%20academia%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fsix-tables-that-tell-the-story-of-academic-unfreedom-in-india%5C%22%3ESix%20Tables%20that%20Tell%20the%20Story%20of%20Academic%20Unfreedom%20in%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKashmir%20and%20academic%20freedom%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20stood%20in%20the%20bottom%2030%25%20among%20179%20countries%20in%20the%20Academic%20Freedom%20Index%20in%202022%2C%20below%20Pakistan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20incident%20also%20brings%20into%20focus%20the%20travel%20restrictions%20imposed%20by%20the%20government%20on%20nearly%20eight%20dozen%20Kashmiri%20academics%2C%20journalists%2C%20lawyers%2C%20political%20activists%20and%20others%20who%20have%20been%20termed%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98threat%E2%80%99%20to%20the%20%E2%80%98security%20of%20the%20state%E2%80%99%20and%20put%20on%20a%20%E2%80%98no-fly-list%E2%80%99%20after%20the%20reading%20down%20of%20Article%20370.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKaul%20co-edited%20%3Cem%3ECan%20You%20Hear%20Kashmiri%20Women%20Speak%3F%20Narratives%20of%20Resistance%20and%20Resilience%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20new%20collection%20of%20essays%20by%20Kashmiri%20women%20on%20the%20themes%20of%20the%20representation%20of%20women%20in%20Kashmiri%20literature%2C%20sexual%20violence%20and%20militarisation%20of%20Kashmir%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%20watering%20down%20of%20Article%20370.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20move%20to%20read%20down%20Article%20370%20%E2%80%9Cdisregarded%20multiple%20United%20Nations%20Security%20Council%20resolutions%2C%20which%20call%20for%20a%20peaceful%20and%20democratic%20solution%20to%20the%20Kashmir%20dispute.%20With%20this%20sleight%20of%20hand%2C%20the%20government%20has%20resuscitated%20an%20old%20strategy%20of%20instrumentalising%20the%20pain%20and%20loss%20of%20Kashmiri%20Pandits%20to%20legitimise%20its%20violence%20against%20Kashmiri%20Muslims%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fopinions%2F2019%2F08%2F22%2Fi-am-kashmiri-pandit-india-must-stop-weaponizing-pain-our-past%2F%5C%22%3EKaul%20wrote%20in%20%3Cem%3EWashington%20Post%3C%2Fem%3E%20on%20August%2022%2C%202019.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20two%20day%20conference%2C%20which%20Kaul%20missed%2C%20was%20held%20on%20February%2024-25%20at%20Palace%20Grounds%20in%20Bengaluru.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EProfessor%20Gopal%20Guru%2C%20editor%20of%20%3Cem%3EEconomic%20and%20Political%20Weekly%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Dr%20S.Y.%20Quraishi%2C%20former%20Chief%20Election%20Commissioner%20of%20India%2C%20Professor%20Nandini%20Sundar%20of%20the%20Delhi%20School%20of%20Economics%20and%20Yamini%20Aiyar%2C%20president%20and%20chief%20executive%20of%20the%20Centre%20for%20Policy%20Research%2C%20were%20among%20eminent%20academics%20and%20historians%20who%20attended%20the%20event.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20letter%20to%20Kaul%20on%20February%205%2C%20Mahadevappa%20noted%20that%20her%20presence%20would%20add%20a%20%E2%80%9Cunique%20vantage%20point%E2%80%9D%20to%20the%20event%20and%20that%20her%20%E2%80%9Cbody%20of%20her%20work%20will%20undoubtedly%20enrich%20the%20conference%20and%20enable%20us%20to%20collectively%20achieve%20our%20shared%20goals.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20conference%20shall%20normatively%20reflect%20on%20broad%20themes%20of%20%E2%80%98Constitutionalism%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98Justice%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98Inclusiveness%E2%80%99%20and%20Identity%E2%80%99%20and%20thereby%20rethink%20current%20socio-economic%2C%20political%20and%20cultural%20paradigms.%20In%20doing%20so%2C%20we%20hope%20to%20collectively%20propose%20innovative%20ideas%20to%20redress%20structural%20problems%20in%20India%20and%20the%20world%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20letter%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20with%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20one%20of%20the%20organisers%20of%20the%20event%2C%20who%20didn%E2%80%99t%20want%20to%20be%20named%2C%20said%20that%20Kaul%20called%20the%20organisers%20at%20around%204%20am%20on%20Saturday%20after%20she%20was%20detained%20by%20the%20airport%20authorities.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Karnataka%20government%20officials%20took%20up%20Kaul%E2%80%99s%20detention%20with%20officials%20of%20the%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20but%20nothing%20came%20out%20of%20it.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CKaul%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20even%20given%20any%20document%20for%20her%20detention.%20It%20was%20only%20the%20airline%20staff%20that%20finally%20gave%20her%20the%20notice%20that%20said%20she%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20permitted%20in%20India%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20organiser%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKaul%20was%20one%20of%20the%20international%20delegates%20who%20was%20supposed%20to%20speak%20in%20different%20interactive%20sessions%20at%20the%20event.%20The%20organiser%20added%20that%20at%20least%20eight%20of%20the%20international%20delegates%20who%20attended%20the%20event%20were%20%E2%80%9Cunnecessarily%20screened%20at%20the%20Bengaluru%20airport%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThey%20were%20asked%20too%20many%20questions%2C%20detained%20for%20hours%2C%20and%20mentally%20harassed%20but%20were%20finally%20allowed%20to%20leave%20the%20airport%2C%E2%80%9D%20they%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20%E2%80%9CKaul%20was%20the%20only%20one%20who%20was%20denied%20permission%20to%20enter%20India.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20logistical%20support%20for%20her%20visit%2C%20including%20her%20travel%2C%20was%20arranged%20by%20the%20government%20of%20Karnataka%2C%20she%20said%2C%20alleging%20that%20the%20airport%20authorities%20didn%E2%80%99t%20provide%20her%20%E2%80%9Cbasic%20things%20such%20as%20a%20pillow%20and%20blanket%E2%80%9D%20while%20she%20was%20in%20the%20holding%20cell%20before%20her%20deportation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3Eand%20no%20easy%20access%20to%20food%20and%20water%2C%20made%20dozens%20of%20calls%20to%20airport%20for%20basic%20things%20as%20a%20pillow%20and%20blanket%2C%20which%20they%20refused%20to%20provide%2C%20then%2012%20hours%20on%20the%20flight%20back%20to%20London.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2Fz6O5Jx2onB%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2Fz6O5Jx2onB%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20Professor%20Nitasha%20Kaul%2C%20PhD%20(%40NitashaKaul)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FNitashaKaul%2Fstatus%2F1761711456058265699%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw