d%20their%20money%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstate-of-payment-methods-more-choice-affecting-how-consumers-spend-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecash%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20actually%20%3Cem%3Enot%3C%2Fem%3E%20king.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.frbservices.org%2Fnews%2Fresearch.html%2F2023-findings-from-the-diary-of-consumer-payment-choice%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2023%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20conducted%20by%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20showed%20that%20the%20credit%20card%20was%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-credit-cards-more-popular-than-debit-cards-2017-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emost%20preferred%20payment%20method%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20US%20consumers%2C%20making%20up%2031%25%20of%20all%20payments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENext%20was%20the%20debit%20card%20at%2029%25%2C%20then%20cash%20at%20third%2C%20making%20up%2018%25%20of%20all%20transactions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20represents%20a%20consistent%20decline%20in%20cash%20payments%20since%20the%20pandemic%20in%202020%2C%20which%20saw%20many%20shifts%20in%20consumer%20behavior%2C%20including%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F100-people-transforming-business-presents-shopping-and-retail-leaders-2021-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eacceleration%20of%20online%20shopping%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202019%2C%2026%25%20of%20payments%20were%20made%20with%20cash.%20The%20following%20year%2C%20the%20study%20showed%20that%20cash%20made%20up%2019%25%20of%20payments%20and%20has%20not%20recovered%20since.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20this%20hasn't%20stopped%20the%20consistent%20churn%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhenry-blodget-how-the-fed-prints-money-2009-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprint%20currency%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffederal-reserve-guide-central-bank-interest-rates-why-should-care-2021-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFederal%20Reserve%3C%2Fa%3E%20data%20shows%20that%20the%20volume%20of%20currency%20in%20circulation%20has%20only%20increased%20since%202002.%20Every%20denomination%20%E2%80%94%20including%20less%20common%20banknotes%20such%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fold-two-dollar-bills-2-worth-currency-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%242%20bill%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20has%20increased%20in%20circulation%2C%20from%20the%20humble%20dollar%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F9-security-features-in-new-100-bill-2013-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBenjamins%3C%2Fa%3E.%20As%20of%20December%2031%2C%20there%20were%2054.1%20billion%20notes%20in%20circulation%20compared%20to%2022.9%20billion%20notes%20in%202002.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ECash%20is%20still%20king%20of%20some%20things%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEconomics%20experts%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Esay%20that%20despite%20increasing%20reliance%20on%20cards%2C%20cash%20remains%20resilient%20and%20an%20important%20payment%20method%20for%20many%20consumers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCash%20still%20remains%20really%20important%20to%20certain%20segments%20of%20consumers%2C%26quot%3B%20Christopher%20Bechler%2C%20assistant%20professor%20of%20marketing%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Notre%20Dame%20Mendoza%20College%20of%20Business%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%2C%20pointing%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Faddressing-unbanked-underbanked-challenges-requires-multifaceted-approach-according-to-new-report-1030441632%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunderbanked%20customers%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20one%20segment%20of%20the%20population%20who%20rely%20on%20cash.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnderbanked%20consumers%20often%20refer%20to%20people%20with%20bank%20accounts%20who%20rely%20on%20alternative%20financial%20services%20such%20as%20non-bank%20money%20orders%20or%20payday%20loans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBechler%20said%20that%20cash%20also%20tends%20to%20be%20a%20preferred%20payment%20method%20for%20smaller%20purchases%20under%20%2410%20or%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%26quot%3Bhard-to-justify%26quot%3B%20items%2C%20referring%20to%20%26quot%3Bguilty%26quot%3B%20purchases%20that%20aren't%20necessary%2C%20like%20an%20overpriced%20water%20bottle%20at%20an%20airport%20or%20cigarettes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.journals.uchicago.edu%2Fdoi%2F10.1086%2F726429%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2023%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20in%20the%20Journal%20of%20the%20Association%20for%20Consumer%20Research%2C%20Bechler%20found%20that%20consumers%20%26quot%3Bpay%20with%20card%20to%20remember%20and%20cash%20to%20forget%26quot%3B%20because%20the%20latter%20method%20won't%20leave%20a%20paper%20trail%20of%20their%20purchases.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20pattern%20is%20strongest%20for%20consumers%20who%20diligently%20track%20their%20card%20spending%20and%20occurs%20because%20consumers%20don't%20want%20to%20see%20records%20of%20their%20unjustifiable%20spending%2C%26quot%3B%20Bechler%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhen%20cash%20is%20burned%20%E2%80%94%20literally%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EConsumer%20demand%20and%20trends%20in%20payment%20methods%20are%20not%20the%20only%20reasons%20the%20government%20continues%20to%20place%20print%20currency%20orders.%20Another%20reason%20is%20to%20replace%20money%20already%20in%20circulation%20that%20has%20been%20destroyed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%26quot%3Bprimary%20driver%26quot%3B%20for%20the%202024%20fiscal%20year%20currency%20print%20order%20%26quot%3Bwas%20the%20need%20to%20replace%20unfit%20notes%20destroyed%20during%20normal%20processing%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20said%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.federalreserve.gov%2Fpaymentsystems%2Fcoin_currency_orders.htm%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520CY%25202024%2520print%2520order%