2F%2Fdigitalcommons.wayne.edu%2Fcgi%2Fviewcontent.cgi%3Farticle%3D2055%26context%3Dhumbiol%5C%22%3EAndaman%20Islands%3C%2Fa%3E%20first%20landed%20there%20at%20least%2025%2C000%20years%20ago%E2%80%94%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.egyankosh.ac.in%2Fbitstream%2F123456789%2F69339%2F1%2FUnit-3.pdf%5C%22%3Eand%20likely%20closer%20to%2060%2C000%3C%2Fa%3E%20years%20ago.%20For%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20years%20they%20successfully%20lived%20in%20sustainable%20balance%20with%20their%20island%20ecosystems%3A%20dots%20of%20land%20with%20clearly%20constrained%20limits%20to%20growth.%20The%20ongoing%20destruction%20of%20their%20cultures%2C%20due%20to%20colonisation%20by%20the%20British%20and%20then%20mainland%20Indians%2C%20undoubtedly%20represents%20the%20loss%20of%20a%20valuable%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scientificamerican.com%2Farticle%2Fthis-ancient-language-has-the-only-grammar-based-entirely-on-the-human-body%2F%5C%22%3Eknowledge%20system%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20how%20to%20live%20on%20Earth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftd%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftbody%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ftable%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20at%20a%20balanced%20rate%20of%20consumption%20and%20waste%2C%20our%20population%20could%20grow%20to%20fill%20the%20carrying%20capacity%20of%20the%20land%E2%80%94that%20is%2C%20the%20number%20of%20humans%20the%20local%20ecosystem%20could%20sustainably%20support%20in%20a%20given%20way%20of%20life%E2%80%94and%20there%20it%20had%20to%20stabilise.%20If%20we%20spoiled%20the%20landscape%20by%20over-extracting%20resources%2C%20over-polluting%2C%20or%20otherwise%20carelessly%20destroying%20the%20integrity%20of%20the%20ecosystem%2C%20we%20would%20overshoot%20the%20land%E2%80%99s%20carrying%20capacity%2C%20impoverishing%20ourselves%20in%20the%20same%20moment.%20The%20feedback%20from%20the%20local%20ecosystem%20in%20response%20to%20such%20%3Cem%3Eecological%20overshoot%3C%2Fem%3E%20could%20be%20quick%20and%20stern%2C%20as%20resources%20then%20declined%20in%20the%20following%20season%20or%20year%2C%20causing%20hunger%20and%20other%20problems.%20Societies%20that%20resisted%20adjusting%20their%20ways%20to%20accommodate%20the%20needs%20of%20the%20ecosystem%2C%20who%20instead%20forced%20their%20environment%20to%20bend%20to%20their%20own%20priorities%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2F3quarksdaily.com%2F3quarksdaily%2F2022%2F02%2Fstories-of-collapse.html%5C%22%3Ewould%20collapse%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2F3quarksdaily.com%2F3quarksdaily%2F2022%2F01%2Fstories-of-continuity.html%5C%22%3ESuccessful%20communities%20learned%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20their%20costly%20mistakes%20and%20adjusted%20their%20lifestyles%20accordingly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20could%20be%20no%20hoarding%20of%20surpluses%2C%20no%20wanton%20annihilation%20or%20dismemberment%20of%20the%20local%20ecosystem%20in%20this%20kind%20of%20%3Cem%3Eimmediate-return%20economy%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20as%20typified%20by%20nomadic%20foraging%20cultures.%20Living%20within%20the%20constraints%20of%20the%20land%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20easily%20allow%20for%20the%20kinds%20of%20socioeconomic%20differentiation%20we%20know%20today.%20Without%20surpluses%20or%20hoarding%2C%20there%20could%20be%20no%20rich%20or%20poor%20people%2C%20no%20persistent%20economic%20stratifications%20or%20classes%20of%20people.%20And%20since%20most%20individuals%20were%20reasonably%20adept%20in%20the%20necessary%20skills%20of%20provision%20and%20survival%2C%20there%20was%20little%20leverage%20for%20tyranny%20or%20coercion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F25113719%2Find-jar-tf-284_gallery_large.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22910%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F25113719%2Find-jar-tf-284_gallery_large.jpg%20910w%2C%20h